paragraphs.title: Shuffle Time Analysis @ attempt level
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName,
       taskAttemptId,
       counterGroup,
       Node,
       SHUFFLE_BYTES,
       TotalTimeTaken,
       TimeTaken_To_Receive_Events,
       SHUFFLE_PHASE_TIME,
       MERGE_PHASE_TIME,
       TimeTaken_For_Real_Task,
       FIRST_EVENT_RECEIVED,
       LAST_EVENT_RECEIVED,
       SHUFFLE_BYTES_DISK_DIRECT
FROM shuffleResult__${dagName}
WHERE counterGroup != 'org.apache.tez.common.counters.TaskCounter' -- AND (SHUFFLE_PHASE_TIME - LAST_EVENT_RECEIVED) > 10000  --(to demo if shuffle is slow due to last event received; ie higher vertex)
ORDER BY cast(SHUFFLE_PHASE_TIME AS int) DESC LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: ShuffleVertexManager Slowstart Analysis (Whether slow start is needed or should be tuned etc, based on fIRST_EVENT_RECEVIED vs LAST_EVENT_RECEIVED)
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName, -- This is just example. Change the query to suite your needs. Might want to try out at vertex level and tweak ShuffleVertexManager slowstart settings
       taskAttemptId,
       'This task got scheduled too soon. Ended up wasting slot' AS description,
       Node,
       ((LAST_EVENT_RECEIVED - FIRST_EVENT_RECEIVED) / TotalTimeTaken) AS wastageRatio
FROM shuffleResult__${dagName}
WHERE counterGroup != 'org.apache.tez.common.counters.TaskCounter'
  AND ((LAST_EVENT_RECEIVED - FIRST_EVENT_RECEIVED) / TotalTimeTaken) > 0.8
ORDER BY cast(wastageRatio AS int) DESC LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: Skew Analyzer (for Shuffle) - To understand issues related to partitioner / parallelism / memory issues based on REDUCE_INPUT_GROUPS / REDUCE_INPUT_RECORDS
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName,
       taskAttemptId,
       counterGroup,
       node,
       SHUFFLE_BYTES,
       timeTaken,
       REDUCE_INPUT_GROUPS,
       REDUCE_INPUT_RECORDS,
       input_records_to_group_ratio,
       observation
FROM skewAnalyzer__${dagName}
ORDER BY cast(timeTaken AS int) DESC
-- For demo, set "tez.skew-analyzer.shuffle.bytes.per.source=100000". But ideally it could be around 100-500 MB atleast per source for better filtering.

paragraphs.title: Container Preemption diagnostics (e.g find number of prematurely killed task attempts done via scheduler. E.g Adjust tez.am.preemption.percentage)
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName,
       "Internal Container Pre-emption" AS description,
       count(*) AS totalPreemptionCount
FROM slowTask__${dagName}
WHERE DIAGNOSTICS LIKE '%preempted%'
  AND status LIKE 'KILLED'
GROUP BY vertexName -- May be we need to find the ratio of total attempts vs pre-emption to understand the wastage??

vertexName	description	totalPreemptionCount
Reducer 3	Internal Container Pre-emption	24

paragraphs.title: SlowTask Identifier - Query slow tasks at every vertex (change SQL filters accordingly)
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName,
       taskAttemptId,
       Node,
       taskDuration,
       Status,
       NoOfInputs
FROM slowTask__${dagName}  WHERE vertexName == "Map 5"  -- For demo, try to analyze the straggler task from Map 5 identified above (notice most of all stragglers ran on same node cn058)
ORDER BY cast(taskDuration AS int) DESC LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: Spill Analysis - Find out if any spills happened in the task (adjust sort buffer accordingly)
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT vertexName,
       taskAttemptId,
       Node,
       counterGroupName,
       spillCount,
       taskDuration,
       OUTPUT_BYTES,
       OUTPUT_BYTES,
       SPILLED_RECORDS,
       Recommendation
FROM spills__${dagName} WHERE counterGroupName != 'org.apache.tez.common.counters.TaskCounter'
ORDER BY cast(taskDuration AS int) DESC LIMIT 1000

paragraphs.title: Slow Nodes - Find out if there any slow nodes in the cluster (Need To co-relate noOfTasksExecuted vs avgTaskExecutionTime vs BytesRead/Written)
paragraphs.text:
%sql SELECT nodeName,
       noOfTasksExecuted,
       noOfKilledTasks,
       noOfFailedTasks,
       avgSucceededTaskExecutionTime,
       avgKilledTaskExecutionTime,
       avgFailedTaskExecutionTime,
       avgHDFSBytesRead,
       avgHDFSBytesWritten,
       avgFileBytesRead,
       avgFileBytesWritten,
       avgGCTimeMillis,
       avgCPUTimeMillis
FROM slowNodes__${dagName} ORDER BY cast(avgSucceededTaskExecutionTime as int) DESC,  cast(noOfTasksExecuted as int) DESC -- demo (cn058 was identified as slow node in Map 5 straggler taskss)
